  <description type="morphology">Leaves ovate-lanceolate to short-subulate from an ovate or obovate base, entire at apex; costa percurrent or subpercurrent.  Seta short, 4–6 mm.  Capsule not or little inclined, slightly curved; neck equaling the urn in length, cylindric or obovate, not strumose but tapering instead; peristome teeth entire or perforate near apex, not fragile, commonly persistent; annulus compound, revoluble.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature late summer–fall.</description>
